Milt M. ANDERSON, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 6394. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Oct. 7, 1932. Joseph G. Collins, of Gainesville, Ga., and W. R. Tucker, of Dawsonville, Ga., for appellant. J. M. Johnson and Hal Lindsay, Asst. U. S. Attys., both of Atlanta, Ga.

Before BRYAN, FOSTER, and WALKER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
